Police on Tuesday arrested a most wanted man in Nairobi suspected of fraud. In a statement on Wednesday, police said they intercepted Abdiqafar Abdirashid Abey at Wilson Airport while awaiting to board a plane to Elwak. "The man is suspected to have defrauded the public millions of shillings, as reported at Nyanchwa Police Station in Kisii," NPS said. Police thanked the public for providing crucial information that led to the timely arrest of the suspect.